{"title_page": "2021 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n'''Group A of the [[2021 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]''', also referred to as the '''South Zone''', will take place in June 2021 in Argentina. The group consists of hosts [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], guests [[Australia national soccer team|Australia]], [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]], record winners [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcf.com.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHEDULE-CA2020-v8-horarios-004.pdf |title=CONMEBOL Copa Am\u00e9rica 2020 schedule |website=[[Colombian Football Federation]] |format=PDF |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305010803/https://fcf.com.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHEDULE-CA2020-v8-horarios-004.pdf |archive-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Teams==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Draw position\n! Team\n! data-sort-type=\"number\"| Appearance\n! Previous best<br />performance\n! [[FIFA World Rankings|FIFA Rankings]]<br />June 2020\n|-\n| A1 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|ARG}} (hosts) || 43rd || data-sort-value=\"1.2\" | '''Winners''' ([[1921 South American Championship|1921]], [[1925 South American Championship|1925]], [[1927 South American Championship|1927]], [[1929 South American Championship|1929]], [[1937 South American Championship|1937]], [[1941 South American Championship|1941]], [[1945 South American Championship|1945]], [[1946 South American Championship|1946]], [[1947 South American Championship|1947]], [[1955 South American Championship|1955]], [[1957 South American Championship|1957]], [[1959 South American Championship (Argentina)|1959 (A)]], [[1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1991]], [[1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1993]]) ||\n|-\n| A2 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|AUS}} (invitee) || 1st || data-sort-value=\"99\" | Debut ||\n|-\n| A3 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|BOL}} || 28th || data-sort-value=\"1.4\" | '''Winners''' ([[1963 South American Championship|1963]]) ||\n|-\n| A4 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|URU}} || 45th || data-sort-value=\"1.1\" | '''Winners''' ([[1916 South American Championship|1916]], [[1917 South American Championship|1917]], [[1920 South American Championship|1920]], [[1923 South American Championship|1923]], [[1924 South American Championship|1924]], [[1926 South American Championship|1926]], [[1935 South American Championship|1935]], [[1942 South American Championship|1942]], [[1956 South American Championship|1956]], [[1959 South American Championship (Ecuador)|1959 (E)]], [[1967 South American Championship|1967]], [[1983 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1983]], [[1987 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1987]], [[1995 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1995]], [[2011 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2011]]) ||\n|-\n| A5 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|CHI}} || 40th || data-sort-value=\"1.32\" | '''Winners''' ([[2015 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2015]], [[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario|2016]]) ||\n|-\n| A6 || style=white-space:nowrap | {{fb|PAR}} || 38th || data-sort-value=\"1.31\" | '''Winners''' ([[1953 South American Championship|1953]], [[1979 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1979]]) ||\n|}\n\n==Standings==\n{{2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica group tables|Group A}}\n\nIn the [[2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Quarter-finals|quarter-finals]]:\n*The winners of Group A will advance to play the fourth-placed team of [[2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group B|Group B]].\n*The runners-up of Group A will advance to play the third-placed team of Group B.\n*The third-placed team of Group A will advance to play the runners-up of Group B.\n*The fourth-placed team of Group A will advance to play the winners of Group B.\n\n==Matches==\n{{Hatnote|All match times listed are local, [[Time in Argentina|ART]] ([[UTC\u221203:00|UTC\u22123]]).}}\n\n===Matchday 1===\n\n====Argentina vs Chile====\n<section begin=A01 />{{Football box\n|date       = {{Start