{"title_page": "2021 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\nThe '''knockout stage of the [[2021 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]''' will begin in July 2021 with the quarter-finals and end on 11 July 2021 with the [[2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica Final|final]] at the [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Mel\u00e9ndez|Estadio Metropolitano]] in [[Barranquilla]], Colombia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fcf.com.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHEDULE-CA2020-v8-horarios-004.pdf |title=CONMEBOL Copa Am\u00e9rica 2020 schedule |website=[[Colombian Football Federation]] |format=PDF |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305010803/https://fcf.com.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/SCHEDULE-CA2020-v8-horarios-004.pdf |archive-date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n''All match times listed are local, [[Time in Argentina|ART]] ([[UTC\u221203:00|UTC\u22123]]) in Argentina and [[Time in Colombia|COT]] ([[UTC\u221205:00|UTC\u22125]]) in Colombia.''\n\n==Format==\nIn the knockout stage, if a match is tied after 90 minutes:\n*In the quarter-finals, [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] is not played, and the match is decided by a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].\n*In the semi-finals, third place play-off and final, extra time will be played (two periods of 15 minutes each), where each team is allowed to make a fourth [[Substitute (association football)|substitution]]. If still tied after extra time, the match will be decided by a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]].\n\n==Qualified teams==\nThe top four placed teams from both groups will qualify for the knockout stage.\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Group\n! width=\"170\" | Winners\n! width=\"170\" | Runners-up\n! width=\"170\" | Third-placed teams\n! width=\"170\" | Fourth-placed teams\n|-\n! [[2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A|A]]\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n|-\n! [[2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group B|B]]\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n| <!--{{fb|}}-->\n|}\n\n==Bracket==\n<section begin=Bracket />{{#invoke:RoundN|N8\n|style=white-space:nowrap|widescore=yes|bold_winner=high|3rdplace=yes\n|RD1=[[#Quarter-finals|Quarter-finals]]\n|RD2=[[#Semi-finals|Semi-finals]]\n|RD3=[[#Final|Final]]\n|Consol=[[#Third place play-off|Third place play-off]]\n<!-- Date-Place|Team 1|Score 1|Team 2|Score 2 -->\n<!-- quarter-finals -->\n|5 July \u2013 [[Estadio Monumental Antonio Vespucio Liberti|Buenos Aires]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Group A||<!--{{fb|}}-->4th Group B|\n|5 July \u2013 [[Estadio Ciudad de La Plata|La Plata]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Runner-up Group A||<!--{{fb|}}-->3rd Group B|\n|4 July \u2013 [[Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Pascual Guerrero|Cali]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Runner-up Group B||<!--{{fb|}}-->3rd Group A|\n|4 July \u2013 [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Mel\u00e9ndez|Barranquilla]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Group B||<!--{{fb|}}-->4th Group A|\n<!-- semi-finals -->\n|8 July \u2013 [[Estadio Mario Alberto Kempes|C\u00f3rdoba]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 33||<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 34|\n|8 July \u2013 [[Atanasio Girardot Sports Complex|Medell\u00edn]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 32||<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 31|\n<!-- final -->\n|12 July \u2013 [[Estadio Metropolitano Roberto Mel\u00e9ndez|Barranquilla]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 35||<!--{{fb|}}-->Winner Match 36|\n<!-- 3rd place -->\n|11 July \u2013 [[Estadio El Camp\u00edn|Bogot\u00e1]]|<!--{{fb|}}-->Loser Match 35||<!--{{fb|}}-->Loser Match 36|\n}}<section end=Bracket />\n\n==Quarter-finals==\n\n===Runner-up Group B vs 3rd Group A===\n<section begin=QF1 />{{Football box\n|date       = {{Start date|2020|7|4|df=y}}\n|time       = 17:00 [[Time in Colombia|COT]]\n|team1      = <!--{{fb-rt|}}-->Runner-up Group B\n|score      = {{score link|2020 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Runner-up Group B vs 3rd Group A|Match 32}}\n|team2      = <!--{{fb|}}-->3rd Group A\n|goals1     =