{"title_page": "Louis, Count of \u00c9vreux", "text_new": "{{ infobox royalty\n| name        = Louis\n| title       = [[Count of \u00c9vreux]]\n| image       = Louis de France 1276-1319.JPG\n| caption     = Tomb effigy of Louis d'Evreux now in the [[Basilica of St Denis]] (he was buried in the now-demolished church of the [[Couvent des Jacobins de la rue Saint-Jacques|Couvent des Jacobins]] in [[Paris]])\n| house       = [[House of Capet|Capet]]\n| father      = [[Philip III of France]]\n| mother      = [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]]\n| spouse      = [[Margaret of Artois]]\n| issue       = [[Marie d'\u00c9vreux]] <br> [[Charles d'\u00c9vreux|Charles, Count of \u00c9tampes]] <br> [[Philip III of Navarre]] <br> Margaret <br> [[Jeanne d'\u00c9vreux|Joan, Queen of France]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth_date|1276|5|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1319|5|19|1276|5|3|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Paris]]\n| religion    = [[Roman Catholicism]]\n}}\n'''Louis of \u00c9vreux''' (3 May 1276 \u2013 19 May 1319, [[Paris]]) was a prince, the only son of King [[Philip III of France]] and his second wife [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]],{{sfn|Henneman|1971|p=xvii}} and thus a half-brother of King [[Philip IV of France]].\n\nLouis had a quiet and reflective personality and was politically opposed to the scheming of his half-brother [[Charles of Valois]]. He was, however, close with his nephew [[Philip V of France]].\n\nHe married [[Margaret of Artois]], daughter of [[Philip of Artois]] and sister of [[Robert III of Artois]], and had five children:\n# [[Marie d'\u00c9vreux|Marie]] (1303 \u2013 31 October 1335), married in 1311 [[John III, Duke of Brabant]]\n# [[Charles d'\u00c9vreux|Charles]] (d. 1336), Count of [[\u00c9tampes]] married [[Maria de La Cerda y Lara|Maria de la Cerda, Lady of Lunel]], daughter of [[Ferdinand de la Cerda, Lord of Lara|Fernando de la Cerda]].\n# [[Philip III of Navarre]] (1306\u20131343), married [[Joan II of Navarre]].{{sfn|Henneman|1995|p=328}}\n# Margaret (1307\u20131350), married in 1325 [[William XII of Auvergne]]\n# [[Jeanne d'\u00c9vreux|Joan]] (1310\u20131370), married [[Charles IV of France]]{{sfn|Henneman|1995|p=328}}\n\n== Ancestry ==\n{{unsourced section|date=April 2019}}\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Louis d'\u00c9vreux'''\n|2= 2. [[Philip III of France]]\n|3= 3. [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]]\n|4= 4. [[Louis IX of France]]\n|5= 5. [[Margaret of Provence]]\n|6= 6. [[Henry III, Duke of Brabant]]\n|7= 7. [[Adelaide of Burgundy (1233\u20131273)|Adelaide of Burgundy]]\n|8= 8. [[Louis VIII of France]]\n|9= 9. [[Blanche of Castile]]\n|10= 10. [[Ramon Berenguer IV of Provence]]\n|11= 11. [[Beatrice of Savoy]]\n|12= 12. [[Henry II of Brabant]]\n|13= 13. [[Marie of Hohenstaufen]]\n|14= 14. [[Hugh IV of Burgundy]]\n|15= 15. [[Yolande of Dreux (Burgundy)|Yolande of Dreux]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book |title=Royal Taxation in Fourteenth-Century France: The Development of War Financing, 1322-1359 |first=John Bell |last=Henneman |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=1971 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia |title=Evreux |first=John Bell |last=Henneman |encyclopedia=Medieval France:An Encyclopedia |editor-first=William F. |editor-last=Kibler |publisher=Routledge |year=1995 |ref=harv}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Capet]]|3 May|1276|19 May|1319}}\n|-\n{{S-vac|reason=[[Crown lands of France|Royal domain]]|last=[[Amaury VI of Montfort|Amaury IV]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Count of \u00c9vreux]]|years=1298\u20131319}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Philip III of Navarre|Philip]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Louis, Count Of Evreux}}\n[[Category:1276 births]]\n[[Category:1319 deaths]]\n[[Category:House of Capet]]\n[[Category:House of \u00c9vreux]]\n[[Category:14th-century peers of France]]\n[[Category:Deaths from typhus]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox royalty\n| name = Louis\n| title = [[Count of \u00c9vreux]]\n| image = Louis de France 1276-1319.JPG\n| caption = Tomb effigy of Louis d'Evreux now in the [[Basilica of St Denis]] (he was buried in the now-demolished church of the [[Couvent des Jacobins de la rue Saint-Jacques|Couvent des Jacobins]] in [[Paris]])\n| house = [[House of Capet|Capet]]\n| father = [[Philip III of France]]\n| mother = [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]]\n| spouse = [[Margaret of Artois]]\n| issue = [[Marie d'\u00c9vreux]] <br> [[Charles d'\u00c9vreux|Charles, Count of \u00c9tampes]] <br> [[Philip III of Navarre]] <br> [[Jeanne d'\u00c9vreux|Joan, Queen of France]]\n| birth_date = {{birth_date|1276|5|3|df=yes}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1319|5|19|1276|5|3|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Paris]]\n| religion = [[Roman Catholicism]]\n}}\n'''Louis of \u00c9vreux''' (3 May 1276 \u2013 19 May 1319, [[Paris]]) was a prince, the only son of King [[Philip III of France]] and his second wife [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]],{{sfn|Henneman|1971|p=xvii}} and thus a half-brother of King [[Philip IV of France]].\n\nLouis had a quiet and reflective personality and was politically opposed to the scheming of his half-brother [[Charles of Valois]]. He was, however, close with his nephew [[Philip V of France]].\n\nHe married [[Margaret of Artois]], daughter of [[Philip of Artois]] and sister of [[Robert III of Artois]], and had five children:\n# [[Marie d'\u00c9vreux|Marie]] (1303 \u2013 31 October 1335), married in 1311 [[John III, Duke of Brabant]]\n# [[Philip III of Navarre]] (1306\u20131343), married [[Joan II of Navarre]].{{sfn|Henneman|1995|p=328}}\n# [[Charles d'\u00c9vreux|Charles]] (d. 1336), Count of [[\u00c9tampes]] married [[Maria de La Cerda y Lara|Maria de la Cerda, Lady of Lunel]], daughter of [[Ferdinand de la Cerda, Lord of Lara|Fernando de la Cerda]].\n# Margaret (1307\u20131350), married in 1325 [[William XII of Auvergne]]\n# [[Jeanne d'\u00c9vreux|Joan]] (1310\u20131370), married [[Charles IV of France]]{{sfn|Henneman|1995|p=328}}\n\n== Ancestry ==\n{{unsourced section|date=April 2019}}\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''Louis d'\u00c9vreux'''\n|2= 2. [[Philip III of France]]\n|3= 3. [[Marie of Brabant, Queen of France|Maria of Brabant]]\n|4= 4. [[Louis IX of France]]\n|5= 5. [[Margaret of Provence]]\n|6= 6. [[Henry III, Duke of Brabant]]\n|7= 7. [[Adelaide of Burgundy (1233\u20131273)|Adelaide of Burgundy]]\n|8= 8. [[Louis VIII of France]]\n|9= 9. [[Blanche of Castile]]\n|10= 10. [[Ramon Berenguer IV of Provence]]\n|11= 11. [[Beatrice of Savoy]]\n|12= 12. [[Henry II of Brabant]]\n|13= 13. [[Marie of Hohenstaufen]]\n|14= 14. [[Hugh IV of Burgundy]]\n|15= 15. [[Yolande of Dreux (Burgundy)|Yolande of Dreux]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book |title=Royal Taxation in Fourteenth-Century France: The Development of War Financing, 1322-1359 |first=John Bell |last=Henneman |publisher=Princeton University Press |year=1971 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite encyclopedia |title=Evreux |first=John Bell |last=Henneman |encyclopedia=Medieval France:An Encyclopedia |editor-first=William F. |editor-last=Kibler |publisher=Routledge |year=1995 |ref=harv}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Capet]]|3 May|1276|19 May|1319}}\n|-\n{{S-vac|reason=[[Crown lands of France|Royal domain]]|last=[[Amaury VI of Montfort|Amaury IV]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[Count of \u00c9vreux]]|years=1298\u20131319}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Philip III of Navarre|Philip]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Louis, Count Of Evreux}}\n[[Category:1276 births]]\n[[Category:1319 deaths